text: I proudly announce the winner of my #bestveggieburgerofamsterdam competition! My absolute favorite vegetarian burger in Amsterdam is (drumroll please).... the Dutch Weed Burger! 🏆  There are so many reasons to like it that I don't know where to start. The patty is one of the few ones that I tried that didn't fell apart. The bun is rich in taste and crispy. The Dutch Weed Burger is fully plant based, so suitable for vegans and great news for our planet. It's also kosher, halal and quite healthy as it contains seaweed and chlorella. And one of the best things about it? It's available at many places throughout the Netherlands, and sometimes even abroad (it'll be in London on October 22nd). I hope that my list inspires you and I'd love to hear your thoughts if you tried one of the veggie burgers on my list!

Heard a story of someone riding over a bridge on the Prinsengracht recently. They did that thing when a tourist potters right in the middle of the road and the rider dings their bell loudly at the last minute and zooms past. Kind of like Tom Cruise in Top Gun flying by unsuspecting air control towers. Well, in this instance, the tourist got so spooked that they leaped out of the way and proceeded to trip over another tourist’s rolling suitcase on their way to the ground.
